"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G=
olden_ratio#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>b<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Mathematicians have studied the golden ratio's properties since anti=
quity. It is the ratio of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regula=
r_pentagon" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Regular pentagon">regular pentag=
on</a>'s diagonal to its side and thus appears in the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Straightedge_and_compass_construction" title=3D"Straigh=
tedge and compass construction">construction</a> of the <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dodecahedron" title=3D"Dodecahedron">dodecahedron</a>=
 and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Icosahedron" title=3D"Icosahe=
dron">icosahedron</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHerz-Fischler199820=E2=80=
=9325_9-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gol=
den_ratio#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHerz-Fischler199820%E2%80%9325-9"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> =
A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_rectangle" title=3D"Golde=
n rectangle">golden rectangle</a>=E2=80=94that is, a rectangle with an aspe=
ct ratio of <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"mwe-math-element=
 mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-ma=
thml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/M=
