n with a given side length</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/De=
cagon#Construction" title=3D"Decagon">Decagon with given circumcircle and D=
ecagon with a given side length</a>.
</p><p>Both of the above displayed different <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Algorithm" title=3D"Algorithm">algorithms</a> produce <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_construction" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"Geometric construction">geometric constructions</a> that determi=
ne two aligned <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line_segment" title=
=3D"Line segment">line segments</a> where the ratio of the longer one to th=
e shorter one is the golden ratio.
</p>
