xhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">XAC</span>.</figcaption></figure>
<p>The triangle formed by two diagonals and a side of a regular pentagon is=
 called a <i>golden triangle</i> or <i>sublime triangle</i>. It is an acute=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isosceles_triangle" title=3D"Isos=
celes triangle">isosceles triangle</a> with apex angle <span class=3D"nowra=
p">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span =
class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: non=
e;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\display=
style 36^{\circ }}">
