lden_ratio#cite_note-livio_plus-84"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>78=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Similarly, although Leonard=
o's <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vitruvian_Man" title=3D"Vit=
ruvian Man">Vitruvian Man</a></i> is often shown in connection with the gol=
den ratio, the proportions of the figure do not actually match it, and the =
text only mentions whole number ratios.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-devlin_85-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_ratio#cite=
_note-devlin-85"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>79<span class=3D"cite=
